{
  "text": "Carriers of the D477G mutation exhibit varying phenotypes including disease severity and age of disease onset. They also display areas of retinal atrophy ranging from the choroid to the photoreceptor layer [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Unlike typical RP patients who present with progressive visual field loss from the mid to far periphery, most carriers of the D477G mutation initially present with a central visual defect [CITATION_3] . Moreover, choroidal atrophy and RPE hypertrophy are frequently observed and distinctive features associated with this mutation [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
